sql:
SELECT AVG(rating) AS average_rating
FROM course_feedback
WHERE course_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- "Provider" refers to an organization offering courses;
- "Participant" refers to an individual enrolled in courses;
- "Completed" status indicates that the participant has finished a course;
- "Average grade" is the mean score received by participants in a course;
- "Attendance average grade" is the mean score for participants who attended the course.

- "blossomed with the most completed participants" refers to courses with the highest number of participants who have completed the course and attended all sessions;
- "flowers (participants)" is a metaphor for the participants enrolled in the courses;
- "at least one completed participant" means the course has at least one participant who has both completed the course and attended all sessions.

- "Top 5 courses" refers to the courses with the highest average ratings;
- "Average rating" is calculated by averaging the ratings given by participants for each course;
- "Providers" are organizations that offer the courses.

- The term "details" includes the course ID, course name, provider name, course date, hours, format, location, and maximum participants;
- "2022 onwards" refers to courses scheduled on or after January 1, 2022;
- "Sorted by the most recent courses" means the results are ordered by the course date in descending order.

- "Garden" refers to the course;
- "Gardener" refers to the participant;
- "How well the gardeners think the gardens are blooming" refers to the average rating given by the participant;
- "How many times they've given their thoughts" refers to the count of feedback entries.

- A participant is considered to have attended a course if the `attendance` field in the `registrations` table is set to 1;
- The `total_hours_spent` is the sum of the hours for all courses a participant attended;
- The `course_count` is the total number of distinct courses a participant attended.

- "shining stars" refers to the top 5 participants with the highest average ratings;
- "praise resounds the loudest" refers to the highest average ratings given by the participants;
- "strength of their applause" refers to the average rating values.

- 'dawn of 2022' refers to the start of the year 2022 (January 1, 2022);
- 'identities' refers to the `participant_id`, `first_name`, and `last_name` of the participants;
- 'latest feedback givers' refers to the participants who provided feedback most recently;
- 'thoughts' refers to the feedback ratings provided by the participants.

- 'Provider A' refers to a specific educational provider in the database;
- 'stars that shine in the sky' is a metaphorical expression for the ratings given by participants in the courses;
- 'courses' refers to educational programs or classes offered by providers.

- "reflections and insights" refers to the feedback, ratings, comments, and improvement suggestions provided by participants;
- "completed in 2022" indicates that the feedback was given within the year 2022, as specified by the `feedback_date` between '2022-01-01' and '2022-12-31';
- "details of their registration and performance" includes the registration date, status, completion date, grade, and attendance.

